&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for motivated, dynamic and amiable individual to deliver support to the CVD Primary Prevention Programme based at our Basildon office. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will support the NHS Health Check programme in accordance to best practice guidelines and policies to GP surgeries and pharmacies across the Essex localities &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role will involve the supporting Practices in achieving individual targets set by Essex County Council. The role will involve performance management, practice visits and supporting practices to achieve set targets.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A car driver is essential. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact Karl Winchester CVD Primary Prevention Lead on 0800 022 4524 option 4 or e-mail &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Karl.winchester@acecic.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Basildon is a large town in south Essex, just 30 miles from central London and 10 miles from Southend on Sea with excellent shopping and recreational activities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Previous applicants need not apply. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
